Nats=====True=====127
A group of pirates attacked and defeated a 147-man garrison on Iki Island in 
this body of water, a part of the larger Toi invasion. A disembarkation in this body of 
water occurred during the Battle of (+) Bun'ei. The Fukuoka Castle was built upon 
this body of water, as was the oldest Shingon temple in Kyushu. This body of water 
often names an engagement in which a Goryeo-allied force was thwarted by the (*) 
kamikaze. A Yuan Dynasty invasion force was defeated in, for the point, what bay, via which 
the Mongols attempted to invade Japan?=====
Hakata Bay =====